The GeoTIFF files in this directory contain a number of examples produced by
Intergraph software.  These files are compatible with Intergraph imaging
products such as Image Viewer, I/RAS C, and Image Analyst; and Intergraph GIS
products such as MGE and GeoMedia.

More information on these products can be found at:
	http://www.intergraph.com/imaging
and
	http://www.intergraph.com/photogrammetry
and
	http://www.intergraph.com/gis

Following are listgeo dumps of the GeoTIFF information for each of the examples
in the directory.  The .tif images are a small 200x200 piece of a SPOT image
(copyright CNES/SPOT Image Corp. 1989) showing the main part of the Intergraph
campus in Huntsville, AL USA as it looked in January 1989.  The images are
stored as 8-bit, untiled, and uncompressed.  The coordinates and values aren't
real - these are just examples to show the tags and keys.
